results.name: Integers in alphabetical order in U.S. English (another version of A004740).
comment: The last term of this infinite sequence is 0. - _Lekraj Beedassy_, Mar 09 2006

The penultimate term using the accepted naming convention would be TWO VIGINITILLION TWO UNDECILLION TWO TRILLION TWO THOUSAND TWO HUNDRED TWO. Because not all numbers have names, the sequence would not truly be infinite. [Matthew Goers, Jan 11 2012]
The sequence does not count spaces and hyphens when alphabetizing. If spaces were counted, eight billion eight million would be after eight billion eight. - _Charles Coker_, Jul 29 2019
